HEADWORD: San Jos scale
<hw>San Jo*s⟦eacute⟧" scale</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A very destructive
scale insect (<spn>Aspidiotus perniciosus</spn>) that infests the apple,
pear, and other fruit trees. So called because first introduced into the
United States at <city><etsep>San Jos⟦eacute⟧</etsep></city>,
California.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sank</ent>⟦br⟧
